      <h2 id="installation">Installation</h2>
      <h3>Windows</h3>
      The program will be installed by default in your local application folder 
      (c:\Users\[User Name]\AppData\Local\[%PROGRAM%]). This means that you don't need
      administrator privileges to install the program.<br />
      The program settings will be stored in your local roaming folder
      (c:\Users\[User Name]\AppData\Roaming\[%PROGRAM%]).
      <h3>Mac OSX</h3>
      After opening the dmg file you can drag and drop the application bundle into your application folder.<br /> 
      The program settings will be stored inside your home folder (~/.[%PROGRAM%]).
      <h3>Ubuntu</h3>
      After a double click on the deb package all dependencies as well as the program will be installed. 
      A launcher will also be added to your system. To start the program open the dash (Windows Key) and type
      the first letters of the programs name. Now the program should be listed in dash and you can
      start it by clicking on the launcher icon.<br />
      The program settings will be stored inside your home folder (~/.[%PROGRAM%]).
