      <h2 id="ftsettings">First Time Settings</h2><br />
      <img src="images/lang/en/ftsettings.png" alt="First Time Settings Dialog" title="First Time Settings Dialog" /><br />
      Please enter your account data there. If you want to have erotic channels displayed in your channel list, 
      check the related checkbox. If you insert your parental code in the lower textfield you can watch these
      channels without the need to enter the parental code. I'd strongly recomment to leave this field blank.
      <b>Please Note: Your parental code is equal to your accounts password as long as you haven't changed this.</b><br />
      This dialog is displayed when you start the program for the first time. You can force the display of this dialog
      if you remove the folder for the programs settings.
      <!-- <div class="toplink"><a href="#top">Top</a></div> -->
      <h2 id="settings">Settings</h2>
      You can enter the settings by pressing following symbol on the GUI: <img src="images/tools.png" alt="Settings" title="Settings" />
      <h3 id="mainsettings">Main Settings</h3><br />
      <img src="images/lang/en/set_main.png" alt="Main Settings" title="Main Settings" /><br />
      In this tab you can change / enter basic program settings:
      <ul>
         <li>Account / Password</li>
         <li>Record Path - Where to save recorded video files?</li>
         <li>Player Path - If you want to start an external player you have to choose the executable file there (optional).</li>
         <li>Stream Server (location) - Choose the nearest one.</li>
         <li>Bitrate - Choose between "Premium", "Standard", "Eco" and "Mobile"</li>
         <li>Buffer - Buffer time in seconds. Increase this value if you encounter problems in video playback (default: 8s).</li>
         <li>Timeshift - Hours between Moscow time and your localtime.</li>
         <li>Language - Takes effect only after saving the settings.</li>
         <li>Reload Logos - If you encounter erros in channel list (e.g. a logo doesn't match the channel) you can reload all channel logos there.</li>
         <li>Fix time offset - Compensates small time difference between the API server and your local computer (default: on).</li>
         <li>Enable Adv. Settings - Enables advanced settings tab (default: off).</li>
      </ul>
      <!-- <div class="toplink"><a href="#top">Top</a></div> -->
      <h3 id="shortcuts">Shortcuts</h3><br />
      <img src="images/lang/en/set_shortcuts.png" alt="Shortcut Settings" title="Shortcut Settings" /><br />
      Here you can change the default shortcuts used in this program. To do so mark a shortcut with the mouse.
      Now press the key combination you want as new shortcut. If the line turns red you already used this
      shortcut for another command.<br />
      You can reset the shortcuts to the default values using the tool button at the lower end of this tab.
      <!-- <div class="toplink"><a href="#about" target="_self">Top</a></div> -->
      <h3 id="advsettings">Advanced Settings</h3><br />
      <img src="images/lang/en/set_advanced.png" alt="Advanced Settings" title="Advanced Settings" /><br />
      In this tab you can change following program settings:
      <ul>
         <li>Proxy Server - Configure a proxy server if you can't connect directly to the internet.</li>
         <li>API Server - Change the API server. Activate this field by pressing <b>Ctrl+Alt+A</b><!-- [%HIDEPROJECT%] (default: [%APISERVER%] {Don't touch it!})[%HIDEPROJECT%] -->.</li>
         <li>Player Module - Player dependent configuration files. Choose between "5_libvlc.mod" and "9_libvlc_odl.mod" (default: 5_libvlc.mod). 
         You can have a look at the module files itself to get an idea what's going on there. Don't touch it if you don't know what you're doing!</li>
         <li>Log Level - Configure what will be written to logfile (default: log everything). If you need help if something doesn't work as you 
         expected - don't change it!</li>
         <li>Shutdown Command - If you want to shutdown your computer (e.g. after timer record) you can insert a command here. 
         For Windows a default command is set.</li>
         <li>Ask for Record Filename - Program will ask you for a filename as soon as you want to record any show (default: off).</li>
         <li>Detach player at startup - If you use an external player it will be detached from [%PROGRAM%]. 
         It then runs as independent process which [%PROGRAM%] can't control at all (default: off).</li>
         <li>Doubleclick starts play - If <b>off</b> play starts as soon as you click on a channel in channel list (default: on).</li>
         <li>Minimize to Systray - If <b>on</b> program will be hidden from taskbar when minimized. 
         An icon in the tasktray will tell about the running program instead (default: off).</li>
         <li>Translit record filename - Transliterates a record filename from cyrillic into latin letters (default: off).</li>
         <li>GPU acceleration - Uses GPU for video decoding (highly experimental, default: off).</li>
         <!-- [%HIDDEN%]
         <li>Show Ads - Show commercials at the begin of a video (VOD). Changeable only in VLC-Record (default: on).</li>
         [%HIDDEN%] -->
      </ul>
